title: Grateful Dead Live at Anaheim Stadium on 1987-07-26
lineage: XLII-S > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged, Andrew F. March 2013
description:
Set 1

Iko Iko, Minglewood Blues, Tons Of Steel, West L.A. Fadeaway, When I Paint My Masterpiece-> Mexicali Blues, Bird Song-> Promised Land

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away

Set 3

Mr. Tambourine Man, Dead Man, Maggie's Farm, Simple Twist Of Fate, Watching The River Flow, It's All Over Now Baby Blue, Chimes Of Freedom, Queen Jane Approximately, Stuck Inside Of Mobile With The Memphis Blues Again, Ballad Of A Thin Man, Rainy Day Women #12 And #35, Gotta Serve Somebody, All Along The Watchtower

Third set with Bob Dylan

reviews.review_text: bad this is poor recording find better source, 1 star for there effort though

AnaCrime! I struggle with some of the audience recordings; I wish I could find a good soundboard. There used to be a full video on YT, but now I only see individual songs. 

I grew up a mile from the stadium. I was 12 years old when this event was taking place. I remember everyone was talking about all the hippies in town. It would have been nice to go. The hippies were lining the 5 and 57 freeways. hahaha I still remember the newscasts. 

PS, the title is a nickname that we locals give to our city haha
